<br>
 Frizz then runs up to the Broodmother and hands in a harness of his own. He gets the quest message, and she again turns toward the giant fort, only to get stuck in the loop once more. He does it AGAIN, and this time the Broodmother despawns. Just poofs.<br>
<br>
I was informed that he was not allowed to respawn her, and Frizz regretfully handed me the no drop harness again, which was all the rules let him do. I was a bit disappointed, but grateful at least that I would not have to do the entire quest over, especially because the initial piece was a gift from a friend.<br>
<br>
With that incident in mind, look at this:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 13.1. Items lost in any Quest will not be reimbursed, regardless of the circumstance. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 13.3. NPC's in Quests that disappear or are killed will not be respawned, nor will items on the NPC's be reimbursed. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
